news_header: Israeli airstrikes on Jabalia refugee camp in Gaza result in significant casualties, including women and children.
news_text: An Israeli attack on the Jabalia refugee camp in Gaza has led to at least 33 deaths and over 85 injuries, according to the Palestinian news agency Wafa. Among the deceased are 20 children and women. The strikes targeted multiple houses and Jabalia square, with the death toll expected to rise as rescue efforts continue. The Gaza Health Ministry reported that 39 Palestinians were killed in strikes across Gaza on Friday, with Jabalia being heavily affected. The majority of the wounded are also reported to be women and children.
